description.author: Susumu Katayama
description.synopsis: Automatic inductive functional programmer by systematic search
description.description:
MagicHaskeller is an inductive functional programming system for Haskell.
This package contains the MagicHaskeller library, which can be used within GHCi or as an API for inductive program synthesis.
It also contains the MagicHaskeller executable that is a standalone synthesis program which can be used interactively or as a backend server,
and the MagicHaskeller.cgi executable that is a CGI frontend for providing the Web interface.

package-flags.name: tfrandom
package-flags.description: Use the tf-random package instead of the random package

package-flags.name: ghcapi
package-flags.description: Enable execution using the GHC API rather than the combinatory interpreter

package-flags.name: readfile
package-flags.description: Enable to read a component library file

package-flags.name: debug
package-flags.description: Force typechecking at each dynamic application

package-flags.name: networkuri
package-flags.description: Find Network.URI in network-uri rather than in network < 2.6 (This is a workaround for the changes made in those packages.)
